Package: bayespred
Type: Package
Title: Pragmatic Bayesian Workflow for Clinical Prediction Modelling
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-05-19
Authors@R:
    person("Mohsen", "Sadatsafavi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "msafavi@mail.ubc.ca")
Description: Implements the pragmatic Bayesian workflow for clinical prediction
    modelling described in Sadatsafavi & Riley (2026). Fits logistic regression
    under four shrinkage priors (flat, Jeffreys, log-F, Bayesian Ridge) and
    computes the posterior mean of predicted probability via Gauss-Hermite
    quadrature, MacKay approximation, or self-projection. The resulting 'bpmfit'
    objects are self-contained: prediction at deployment time requires only
    base R, with no dependency on mgcv or brglm2.
